Head and thorax (color). Ground color dark brown with ochraceous markings. Crown (
Fig. 10
) ochraceous with four dark brown maculae: one pair of elliptical spots equally distant between eyes and median line, contiguous to pronotum, and one transverse mark behind each eye. Face (
Fig. 26
) with ochraceous macula extending from one antennal ledge to the other one. Genae with pair of ochraceous markings on outer margins. Pronotum (
Figs 9–10
) with posterior 0.25 area ochraceous. Mesoscutellum with ochraceous lateromedial markings. Forewings (
Figs 9–10
) chocolate brown, except parts of inner claval veins, claval commissure, costal margin, claval suture, ochraceous; hyaline area along costal area in middle. Legs (
Fig. 9
) ochraceous.

Morphology. Sternal apodemes (
Fig. 77
) of second abdominal segment extending to third sternum, elongate, separated from each other by a distance half their width at midlength.

Male genitalia.
Pygofer (

Fig. 
41

), in lateral view, with posterior margin broadly rounded with scattered minute tubercles (

Fig. 
78

), and with a few scattered setae. Subgenital plates broad basally, tapering apically, without long hair-like setae. Styles (

Fig. 
49

), in dorsal view, with inner fork bilobate apically, and outer fork with broad hooked apex; shaft with distal area bearing scattered setae. Connective (

Fig. 
65

) well developed and highly sclerotized, about as broad anteriorly as midlength, and not fused to aedeagal base. Aedeagus (

Fig. 
54

), in ventral view, symmetrical, simple, rather V-shaped in lateral view, preatrium and dorsal apodeme well developed, shaft slightly curved at midlength, in caudal view (

Fig. 
65

) with apical well developed invagination and lateral margins slightly sinuate; gonopore subapical on ventral margin. Anal tube (

Fig. 
41

), small, in lateral view, with segment X bearing pair of elongate processes strongly curved dorsally, forming right angle at basal half, with apical hook; outer margin of hook with two short projections: distal one spiniform and proximal one digitiform.
